*-s: dig, resize

-k: lock, open, passwd, setkey, resize, bury, exhume

*-n'[do not process hooks found in tomb]: open, close

*-p'[preserve ownership of files in tomb]': open

-o'[mount options used to open]' \
-o: options passed to commands: open, lock, forge (see man):
	*--> in forge: specify cipher algo for key generation
	*--> in lock: specify cipher specification
	*--> in open: specify mount options

-f'[force operation]': open
--force
	--> wo überall?

-g'[use a GnuPG key to encrypt a tomb key]': forge, lock, open, passwd, setkey (resize), bury

-r'[provide GnuPG recipients (separated by comma)]': follows -g; forge, lock. passwd, setkey (resize), bury

-R'[provide GnuPG hidden recipients (separated by comma)]' \


*--kdf'[specify the KDF method]': forge
	--> optionaler Param? (--kdf=19 oder so)

*--use-urandom: forge

*--get-mount‐point: list

